    "content": "# Hasana Product Docs\n\nThis folder contains product and requirements documents for Hasana, a garden-first worship consistency app for young Muslims.\n\nThe current MVP centers on a private lifelong garden for Fajr, Dhuhr, Asr, Maghrib, Isha, Quran, Adhkar, and Witr. Core worship logging is local-only, account-free, and does not require network access. The support/payment surface is disabled for MVP and must not process payments or collect payment information.\n\nProduct language should stay gentle in Arabic and English. These docs avoid medical claims, religious authority claims, privacy claims beyond the implemented local-only model, and payment claims beyond the disabled placeholder.\n\n## Current Documents\n\n- [2026-05-26 Hasana Product SRS](2026-05-26-hasana-product-srs.md): approved MVP source of truth for the garden-first scope, core practices, local persistence, acceptance criteria, and deferred future scope.\n- [2026-05-25 Hasana Gamified Garden Requirements - English](2026-05-25-hasana-gamified-garden-requirements-en.md): idea-phase requirements for the lifelong worship garden.\n- [2026-05-25 Hasana Gamified Garden Requirements - Arabic](2026-05-25-hasana-gamified-garden-requirements-ar.md): Arabic version of the idea-phase garden requirements.\n- [Hasana App Store Readiness](app-store-readiness.md): concrete checklist for App Store metadata, privacy answers, disabled payment support, manual QA, and remaining submission tasks.\n\n## Status Convention\n\n- Idea-phase: product direction and unresolved decisions.\n- Draft: actionable enough for design and implementation planning, but still open to review.\n- Approved: ready to drive sprint scope and acceptance criteria.\n",
